h] Upgrade the Hourly Report to Read the Unified Alpha Snapshot So Reporting Stops Reassembling Partial Market Context by Hand\n\n**Task:** Take one real downstream consumer and switch it from narrow ad hoc reads toward the enriched unified alpha snapshot we have been building.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Chose `scripts/hourly-report.sh` as the downstream consumer.\n- Patched it to read from `research/alpha-signals.json` not just for Fear & Greed, but also for:\n  - `pm_risk_context.pm_risk`\n  - `funding_squeeze.direction`\n  - `liquidation_signal.direction`\n- Verified the rendered report snippet now includes the enriched context:\n  - `PM risk: LOW`\n  - `Signals: squeeze=SHORT_SQUEEZE | liq=neutral`\n- This means the reporting layer now reflects the consolidated alpha surface instead of forcing each consumer to manually rediscover signal state.\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is the right next P4 move because pipeline work is only real once something downstream actually consumes it. The hourly report was still acting like alpha-signals was just a Fear & Greed cache",
